The paper deals with interference management in a MIMO interference channel, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The proposed mechanism is based on stable matching, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.SY). The paper also involves the use of algorithms (cs.MM) to reach the stable matching.
